Show HN: GPT-Shell – An AI-Powered Bash Shell
text:
Hello HN folks!

I've been working on a side project called GPT-Shell, an AI-powered command-line interface that aims to revolutionize the way we interact with our development environment. I'm thrilled to share this early, slightly buggy, but functional open release with you all!

GPT-Shell leverages state-of-the-art language models to interpret natural language inputs, allowing you to write code, perform complex tasks, or even troubleshoot issues using simple, human-like commands. While it's still a work in progress, I believe that it has the potential to make our lives as developers easier and more efficient.

Keep in mind that this is a first release, and it might have its quirks. I'd appreciate any feedback, suggestions, and bug reports from you—the passionate and knowledgeable tech community—to help me refine and improve GPT-Shell further.

Feel free to dive in, explore, and let me know what you think. I'm eager to hear your thoughts and collaborate on taking this project to the next level!

Happy coding, Kelsey

title: How to evaluate AI based solutions for your team?
text:
Hello everyone, I recently created a requirement matrix for applying AI solution to our functional workflow. Different criteria of evaluating AI for business use case, I wanted to share it with this community.

In this solution requirement <> vendor matrix, you'll find categorized items of - Features / UI needed for customer support use cases - Reporting and analytics for business KPIs - Data and integration to customer support software - Administration and Security systems for team management

This document is aimed at managers and directors looking to evaluate different AI-based solutions available in market and help improve productivity of their teams.

If you're currently looking for AI solution, I'm happy to share the document and discuss how can we improve evaluation? Ping me in this thread or DM me.
